725767f-a.title: Queens: 102nd Street - 23rd Avenue
725767f-a.text:
102nd Street, west side, between Twenty-third and Twenty-fourth
Avenues, showing in three views the Strong farn outbuildings. Owners
of the place were Mrs. A. Strong, 1852, Mrs. J. Strong, 1860; and
Benjamin Strong, 1873-1891. Simon Remsen born 1848 married a
dauchter of Daniel Rapelje and occupied his father-in-law's farm
on Bowery Bay. Simon Remsen's daughter married James Strong. The
land is now (1927) covered with 2 story dwellings.
May 1923
View 1,2 and 3
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
